	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Bredasdorp - The 27-year-old man arrested for the murder of
his teenage girlfriend is expected to appear in the Bredasdorp Magistrate's
Court on Tuesday. Elba Japhta, 14, was found dead under the man's bed in his
Zwelitsha home on Sunday. She had reportedly been beaten and stabbed to death. Police told News24 the girl had been living with the
suspect. According to locals, she had been in a relationship with the
man for the past two years. The murder comes two years after the murder of Bredasdorp
teenager Anene Booysen, who was found raped and disembowelled in February 2013.
She later died at the Tygerberg Hospital. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  